      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BEER BARON (7) improved sharply second-up when jumping out of the ground late to only be beaten a head over this track and trip. Strips fitter third-up and should be launching late again. INDECISIVE (4) chased gamely into the placings when resuming off a long break last time at Kembla Grange. Wary of a flat effort second-up but he looks to be back in good order. DITTERICH (3) is proving frustrating for his supporters but is ticking along nicely. Doesn't need to improve much to break through. LA MER BLEUE (5) returns from a short break and makes his stable debut for the McRae camp. Was a tough all the way winner before the break and looks to be back in good order off his lead-up trial. Can make a bright start in the new colours.",
